        {
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Button variants",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Each button variant has a particular function and its design signals that function to the user. It is therefore very important that the different variants are implemented consistently across products, so that they message the correct actions.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Mode",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "bold"
                        }
                      ],
                      "text": "Success",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " - For the principal call to action on the page. Primary buttons should only appear once per screen (not including the application header, modal dialog, or side panel).",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "bold"
                        }
                      ],
                      "text": "Info",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " - For secondary actions on each page. Secondary buttons can only be used in conjunction with a primary button. As part of a pair, the secondary button’s function is to perform the negative action of the set, such as “Cancel” or “Back”. Do not use a secondary button in isolation and do not use a secondary button for a positive action.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "bold"
                        }
                      ],
                      "text": "Warning",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " - For less prominent, and sometimes independent, actions. Tertiary buttons can be used in isolation or paired with a primary button when there are multiple calls to action. Tertiary buttons can also be used for sub-tasks on a page where a primary button for the main and final action is present.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "bold"
                        }
                      ],
                      "text": "Danger",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " - For actions that could have destructive effects on the user’s data (for example, delete or remove).",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "bold"
                        }
                      ],
                      "text": "Alert",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " - For actions that could impact other settings indirectly.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "bold"
                        }
                      ],
                      "text": "Special",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " - For special or unique actions; often used in conjunction with a primary button.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "type": "listItem"
            }
          ],
          "type": "bulletList"
        },
